DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
Context("Numeric");
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(5,15,1);
$b1 = random(2,8,1);
$c1 = random(2,7,1);
$d1 = random(2,6,1);
$n1 = random(3,7,1);
$x1 = random(1,5,1);

$funct1 = Compute("($a1)*(-$n1)*x^(-$n1-1)");

BEGIN_TEXT
If \( f(x) =  \frac { $a1 } {x ^{ $n1 } } \), find \( f'( x ) \).
$BR$BR Answer: \{ans_rule(25) \}
END_TEXT

ANS($funct1->cmp);

$showHint=-1;
BEGIN_HINT
Use the power rule.  Rewrite the function using a negative power.  That's a good tactic to help do these correctly, especially if the function is \(\frac{1}{x}\).
END_HINT
